{
  "stem": "7506.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "A barrack that was in a completely separate part of the camp, where I'd never been.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were told to go in that barrack.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we found ourselves bunks and laid down.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a couple of women-- older women who weren't Dutch, who didn't speak Dutch, and we only spoke Dutch, because we were Dutch-- they kind of started-- how could I say?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like, getting busy with us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, like, helping us take our clothes off and laying down or saying, go in that bunk.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that's-- that day and the day before, I think are the worst days, up to then, in my life, when my sister and I were left alone with the other children.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And not with our parents and not with any people that we knew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not with any people from Holland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Only the children.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As the women I saw-- there may be been two or three women-- they were not Dutch.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were either Polish or German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At that time I didn't know what they were, but I knew they weren't Dutch.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They didn't speak Dutch.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Only Dutch people speak Dutch.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And from that time, I never saw my father ever again.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And at that time, I never saw my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I then didn't see my aunt anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I didn't see my cousin anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was just with Helen, my sister, and the children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we were together then all the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were together all the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her bunk was like that, and my bunk-- I think my bunk was underneath, which was lower to the floor.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if I remember, in that barrack, we only had two, not three.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
